hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Just had two nights in this hotel and I really wouldn’t recommend anyone staying there at the moment unless you like being outside a building site! The roads are being dug up outside and digging starts at 7am! Only wanted two days of rest and was a complete nightmare, when asked the receptionist if we could move rooms she was so rude. We wasn’t informed this was going on before we travelled here had I known I certainly wouldn’t of booked.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Passy is an excellent neighborhood to stay in when visiting Paris. This hotel is well-managed and our room was larger than expected, incredibly clean, and comfortable. The deep tub was so nice after a day of sight-seeing. There was room for us to sit and have breakfast at a small table and chairs right by the window, looking out at the Parisian building across the street. There is a mini-bar which we used as a mini-fridge by kicking out the drinks during our stay. No microwave in the room, but the front desk was happy to heat up food in a microwave when asked.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
The location of the hotel was exactly as I had hoped.
The room was very nice with a large bathroom
We had the small breakfast each morning and everything was fresh and good value for the price
Staff was very courteous and helpful
I would recommend this hotel to friends

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Charming hotel staff very helpful. Nice neighborhood to walk and close to parks, shopping, restaurants and tourist sites. Room was well appointed. Breakfast is minimal but freshly prepared. Would happily stay again.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: As advertised. Friendly, professional team that was sincere and engaged in wanting to make sure we had a good stay, and very Parisian. Clean, quaint and charming place in the middle of everything. Surprisingly special - Best Western at its Best. Would stay again if travels brought back to this part of Paris.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
paris from los angeles with kids during spring break 2023.
cons: extra small elevator which fits 2-3 w/o luggage.. older building
pros: comfortable beds and very quiet. 5 min walk to metro. 5 min walk to farmers market, alley next to Mc Donalds, must visit.
I would definitely go back.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We stayed in a family room (no.45). The room was a nice size and the bathroom was particularly chic. The hotel staff were friendly and we were surprised to find our room cleaned daily after we came home from sightseeing! The hotel is in a good location and the Eiffel Tower is so close. Favourite bar was really friendly. Thanks for a lovely stay.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: I have stayed in this hotel many times over the years for business trips to Paris. I keep returning because it is a lovely hotel with a great breakfast and helpful staff. The hotel is also very well priced for it's location and amenities. The hotel is well-located in the 16th near two Metro lines, making it easy to get around the city. It is also very easy to walk down to the Trocadero and Eiffel Tower. The hotel is also in the middle of several great restaurants, stores and pastry shops on Passy. The rooms are always well-maintained with a comfortable bed and are a nice size for Paris hotel rooms. I particularly enjoy the breakfast, which I think is well-priced for coffee/tea and a nice selection of eggs, breakfast meats, yogurts, and yummy pastries. The front desk staff is always extremely helpful confirming reservations, making restaurant recommendations, and reserving taxis to the airport. Definitely looking forward to returning!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
*It is a compact stay, with cozy, clean rooms and supportive staff. You get breakfast, though no lunch or dinner. However, based as it is near the Passy Market, you are not short on choices.

The breakfast is simple, with ample choice. I visited Paris on a conference, hence the stay at BWP was comfortable and helped me concentrate on the conference.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
The place is very nice, the rooms pretty, clean, warm...
BUT
We were a group of several colleagues for work, but there was always something that had a technical issue in each room: one has the fridge broken, one has the kettle not working, one has the bathtub lid issue etc... for the price we pay, I was expecting for a higher quality.
Also, the check-in time is really very long. In other hotels, they prepare the arrival of the guests but in this hotel, they start the preparation at the arrival, which is not time-efficient AT ALL. We need to count at least 10 min for check-in and when you are a group, it can be very long.
The hotel is very heartwarming, so I hope these comments would be taken into account in the future.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Our family totally enjoyed our stay in Paris. The Trocadero de Tour Hotel was centrally located which gave us easy access to the sites of Paris. The staff at the Trocadero was fabulous. We felt very at home with their kindness and helpfulness. We must mention Alexi. A true gentleman. Alexi was a treasure trove of information about Paris and it's surroundings. Carole at reception was extremely nice and helpful to us as well. We were always greeted with a warm smile by hotel breakfast staff. Thank you all for making our trip to Paris special. We hope to return to visit Paris again soon.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Very helpful staff, good location. Don't confuse this hotel with the other best western hotel trocadero nearby, like I did. Comfortable room, and surprisingly quiet at night. Plenty shops and restaurants nearby.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Helpful staff, nice and spacious rooms, great location. We traveled as a family of 4 and slept comfortably in the room. We enjoyed walking distance to many great sights and easy access to the metro. Lobby was very nice and historic. It really added something to our visit.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We went for my 30th birthday 🥳 it was an amazing hotel. I plan on coming back to this hotel. Great location. Hotel staff was amazing and so helpful, and gave great advice on what to see and helped set up a driver for us.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Located near Eiffel Tower about 15 minute walk or so but also in a quiet area on a quiet street. We had never seen an elevator that small but added to the charm of the hotel. The employee who checked us in (Delphine) was very efficient and helpful with maps of area and suggestions of what attractions to see as well as walking directions, train directions etc. Because of her, we decided to visit Disney Paris (FANTASTIC by the way) and she was instrumental in ordering our tickets for us on line as well as directions to the subway. We liked our room accommodations and beds were comfortable. Loved the reception area of lobby and enjoyed cocktails before heading out one evening. The only negative was we chose the hotel based on we thought daily breakfast was included as per description on line (slightly misleading) but no, not so. I brought it to their attention but they didn’t add it complimentary and we chose not to eat there simply for that reason. Other than that, we recommend this place.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
We are longtime Best Western Platinum members and stay in BW hotels as much as we can. This was our 5th trip to Paris in the last 10 years; this time to celebrate a birthday of a close family member. We chose this hotel first because it was close to our family's home and located in a "non-touristy" area and had an authentic feel of a "local" feel. We loved the Passy neighborhood which is a 10 minute walk to Eiffel Tower on the north side. To give you an idea, we have stayed in at 5 star and 4 star properties in our last 4 trips. This is CERTAINLY not a 4 star hotel. The French rating system was having an OFF day when they rated this hotel.
We had requested long in advance for an early check in (understanding that it was upon availability). No such luck. The reception person informed us that we had to wait about 4 hours to check in, so we went to have lunch and explore the neighborhood. When we checked in, we found our room (a Classic room) to be the absolute SMALLEST room that we have ever stayed in over 50+ hotel rooms in Europe in the last 10 years! I replied to a "Check-in" survey email upon our first night about our experience. I mentioned the room size and the reply from the front desk was that" even though the BW reservation and the French rating system allows for such a small room ( CLASSIC Room) for double occupancy the hotel does NOT recommend it! BW SHOULD NOT offer this room for double occupancy. PERIOD! It left a bad taste in our stay.
Couple of small notes: the elevator barely fits one person with a normal suitcase otherwise get ready to take the spiral stairs (up to 7 floors) .The tiles on the shower had mold and mildew stains on the The front desk personnel hesitated to engage in any conversation as much we tried to have one.
I would not recommend this hotel.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
Hotel in general is very clean and neat.
My stay was grat, the team was very surportive and attentive. The room is a bit small, but quite cozy. I had to addtionally ask for conditioner, nody lotion at the reception. It would be nice to have them in the room.
Specially thank you for the mager who is very helpful!
I would recomment it to my friends.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: I arrived at this hotel by recommendation of a good Parisian friend. Located off of a busy, centric street (Rue de Passy), but at walking distance from Place du Trocadero and the Eiffel Tower, it's a small hotel that does everything right. It's super safe and clean. The room was as small as you'd expect for a Parisian hotel of this kind, but super comfortable and everything worked perfectly. The staff was specially nice and helpful, going well beyond the call of duty to assist us in everything we needed. Will return for certain. Will return for sure.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Great little hotel. Excellent facilities, great location, very clean, good breakfast, helpful and friendly staff. Couldn’t ask for anything more. Would definitely recommend and wouldn’t hesitate to return. Many thanks.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
I stayed at the hotel on the seventh floor, my room was very comfortable and beautifully decorated. At the reception they always helped if I had questions, thanks to Ekaterina for her care during breakfast and for the omelette specially prepared for me. Very valuable.
Excellent staff, I will definitely return to this hotel.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
It was a great stay at the hotel. Very nice and clean room, we had super bed .I would like a bit bigger balcony but it’s ok . The staff is lovely, some of the girls don't speak French, but their attitude and care was felt in every move and look. Thanks for this . Thanks to the manager for his concern, he was always interested in our well-being and helped if we had a were questions. Great attitude.
Staff are very important, this hotel have a very nice staff , great job , we felt like we are home.
I will recommend this hotel to my friends .

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: The Hotel is very convinient as it is close to OECD and Trocadero as well, with good public transport to the heart of Paris. The location is quiet, no noise at all. The staff is polite and helpful. The breakfast is tasty and abundant. The only inconvinience is the small elevator.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
Nice hotel on a quiet street of Paris but well located in Passy. Rooms were comfortable and good sized for a Triple Rome in Paris. Very comfortable beds

The location couldn’t be any better and quiet, very close to shopping and restaurants

We will stay in this hotel when we return to Paris.

Only the breakfast needs improvement, but La Favorite is a great place for breakfast just a couple os blocks away

Definitively recommend the hotel, extremely well located in a quiet and peaceful area of Paris, with a great location to visit tourist sites

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: I have stayed at Trocadero LaTour since the early 80's whenever I return to Paris, usually every 2 years. I love the Passy neighborhood, the hotel has the flavor of turn of the century Paris in a fine old building with comfortable classic rooms and BIG bathrooms. The price is very reasonable for a fine hotel with an excellent, helpful staff.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
Loved the village quality of the neighbourhood within the city
This hotel is very nicely located.

Very nice staff, supportive and generous

Good memory of the stay, rooms are exquisitely decorated
Will recommend for sure only to best friends :)

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
This is a very nice hotel: rooms are lovely, superior rooms have 2 single beds and bathrobes, it is very close to Trocadero, Passy, La Muette in a vibrant area but on a silent street.
Receptionists are service-minded and nice, but to mention what did not work this regarded communication and information between the different teams. Bathrobes are important - we bring them from home if not provided. I noticed that there were none in our room. They would bring them. After asking THREE more times we got the info that there were none left. Bad planning, bad communication.
The second thing was that we arrived at 12, no rooms ready. Check-in was supposed to be at 2, so ok. Went for lunch, coming back at 2, room still not ready. Took another 30 mins. This is also bad planning: if a guest has arrived early, at least make sure the room is ready at the established time.
This has happened twice in this hotell, so maybe there is an issue that could be improved? We are willing to give them a new try, already booked. Fingers crossed: bathrobes in the room, room available at 2!
Still: very nice hotel, rooms, location and friendly staff!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We have enjoied our stay at this cosy and very well presented hotel. Impressed by the friendliness of staff and how clean and tidy the room was. Its a short walk away from the iconic tower with nice little caffe's and restaurants. Staff even helped us park in a secure location. Well pleased with everything. Great job guys!!!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We had a lovely room at the front of the hotel with a small balcony. Very clean and comfortable. We have been staying at this hotel for many years and it is always just as good. Great location near the Trocadero with very convenient Metro stations. We love it and will stay there next time we are in Paris.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
A girlfriend, and I with our daughters in tow visited 5 countries in 17 days. We toured through Europe with our last stop being Paris.
The hotel was nice, comfortable, clean and the front desk staff was friendly overall. Then comes the elevator, or 'lift'. The first day we get there, we are tired from travelling. the elevator is very small, so my 15 year old daughter goes up with a bag to our room on the 3rd floor. She comes back down, and the elevator door will not open. She is panicking, as it is very hot and small. The front staff tell us the maintenance guy is close, and he will get her out shortly. 20 min later, he comes, and its fixed. We called her to calm her down.
The front desk staff tell us we have to wait for a click or the door gets stuck. We ask why they didn't tell us this sooner?

We avoid the elevator for the rest of our stay.
The day comes when we are to leave. We go for breakfast and bring two suitcases down to make bringing luggage down easier. Our transfer to the airport is waiting outside. We have heavy bags, and the spiral staircase would have been hard to manage with our luggage.
We go up in the lift to get the last of our bags. The elevator gets stuck between floors 2 and 3 for over an hour. No one even noticed the alarm for at least 10 minutes. A front desk woman comes on the intercom and says the maintenance guy is 30 minutes away. by the time he gets there, we are in there for over an hour. Sweating, crying, phoning Air Canada... Maintenance guy arrives, and the door is pulled open, still between floors.
We were pulled out between floors by our wrists and told that cabs had been called to get us not the airport as we had sent our transfer away. At this point, we were 90 min behind schedule. We begged the airport staff to let us through the line so we could make our plane.
We were never offered an apology, a free night, anything. In fact, we felt like they blamed us for taking 'too many bags' when it was just two people in the elevator when it got stuck. Terrible end to my amazing trip, and a black mark on Best Western as a whole in my opinion.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
This hotel steal your money in your bags. Keep ALL in safebox or better in your car. Our childrens money as well got stolen from this hotel in our bags.
The breakfast is too expensive and they tried to charge us for the minibar we never touched.
Find another hotel👍🏼

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
We really enjoyed our stay at the Trocadéro La Tour. It’s in an excellent location for the tourist spots whilst being in a quiet street. The room was a good size, well kept and clean.
A couple of very minor things; we tried to get a cup of tea from the bar one evening and were told that there were not enough staff to be able to do this; though alcoholic drinks weren’t a problem. We had breakfast at the hotel one morning and the food was a standard continental buffet breakfast. However the one lady working in the breakfast room was difficult to get hold of - again probably down to numbers of staff available.
We had good recommendations from the staff for a local restaurant to eat one evening, and the staff generally were helpful and polite.
We’d definitely return in the future, and we’d recommend this hotel for others on a similar holiday.

Hayley & Leon Dumont

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We stayed here for 3 days from July 18th thru 21st. Hotel location was great - walking distance to Effiel Tower and also to many local eateries. The room size was small, but clean.- we were a company of 3 and space was a bit of a premium. The Room had AC which not all hotels in Paris have which was great as we visited during a heatwave where the temperatures reached above 100F. Overall a good experience. Watch out for the petite elevator that will require multiple trips to get your baggage to your room.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We enjoyed our stay at the BW Premier Trocadero La Tour as it was close to two major metro stops (Passy and La Muette) which allowed us to get to most sites easily. The hotel itself was situate don a quick street but close to nice restaurants and shopping. The room was very clean and the WiFi worked well. We did not eat the breakfast each morning as we wanted to experience all the cafes and patiserries had to offer. The staff was very nice and helped us find a gym nearby to work out in. We would definitely stay here again!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We stayed here for 8 nights in July. The hotel was quiet, and oh so quaint tucked in just off of Rue de Passy. We were just a short walk to the metro, Boulangerie & shopping. The staff was always helpful in assisting with travel questions and anything we needed. I would recommend this place to anyone! The bed was comfy, the room was clean & we felt very safe. I wish we were still there!!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
There were 6 in my party and our family dog and we all loved the hotel. Close to the sights, comfortable, attractively decorated, dog friendly, managed to park directly outside the hotel.

Top tip : roadside metered parking is free from Sat 8pm and all day Sunday!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
The staff, location and amenities were just what we wanted and needed during our visit. Efficient check in. The elevator is small, faster to use the stairs.
You can easily walk to wonderful restaurants, shopping, the Seine, Eiffel Tower, gardens and parks.
Our room was quiet and provided the ambience of a Parisienne visit.
Our bathroom was well equipped with towels and fine toiletries.
Our bed was very comfortable.
We will stay at this property again and we will encourage others to as well.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: The location of this hotel is perfect for walking to other areas of Paris. It is close to two metro stops. The neighborhood is residential but offers excellent shopping and dining. The hotel was very clean, beds were so comfortable and the staff was very helpful.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
We loved our stay at the Best Western Trocadero La Tour (do note there are two BW properties close to the Eiffel Tower - make sure to confirm your address!). We stayed in a Family Room with my wife and I and our two daughters and the room was plenty big for the 4 of us. Note that you’re getting European size rooms which get even smaller in somewhere as pricey as Paris but we were able to fit comfortably for our 4 night stay.

This room had the queen(?) bed along with two rollaways for our girls that they said were very comfortable. We were on the 6th floor and fortunately there was an elevator (it’s tiny - 3 people or 1 with all the bags was a squeeze) but our girls loved using the spiral staircase.

The bathroom was bigger than expected with two sinks and mirrors and a shower tub. The tub only had glass covering the first half so use caution when showering as it’s easy to soak the floor if you aren’t paying attention to where water is spraying!

The location is awesome - off a side street from the very cool Rue de Passy (we loved the Passy district!) so nice and quiet at night. Passy has tons of shopping and restaurants all within an easy walk from the hotel as well as two metro options (one with the RER) also close by. The Eiffel Tower is also a short walk down Rue de Passy which was a really nice surprise.

All of the staff we met were fantastic and had great recommendations for restaurants or any other questions we had. We did not get the breakfast so can’t comment on that. We would definitely consider staying here again on our next trip to Paris!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Great Hotel. Great lobby. Great neighborhood. Staff very helpful. In walking distance to Eiffel Tower, Easy access to trains and subway. Airlines lost our luggage and desk provided assistance in getting it back.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
This hotel has lots of character. It suited our needs as it is not far from the metro and it was an easy walk to Trocadero gardens and the Eiffel tower. We booked a superior room which although not huge was more than adequate and comfortable. Due to the age of the building there is only a small lift. A bit of a squeeze for 2 people with luggage.
The public rooms are very small but are different to the usual corporate chains. Reception, lounge, TV room and bar are all in the same shared space. The hotel does not have a restaurant. There was some pre packed food in a fridge but it did not appear particularly appetizing. There are a couple of bar/restaurants that we found within easy walking distance and a McDonalds. The hotel does serve breakfast in an area off the lounge/bar.
It was more than adequate for our needs. Cereal, fruit, cold meat, cheese, breads, pastries, juice and coffee. There was also some hot food - sausages, bacon and scrambled egg which we did not try. As breakfast is from 7 - 11 keeping good fresh may present problems.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Hotel location is great, it is walking distance from Trocadero and the Eiffel tower (10-15 minutes), and close to metro stations Passy and La Muette. The staff is very nice. They even provide you with a before-arrival survey where you can indicate any need you may have. The hotel is in an old building but has a small elevator. The rooms are very clean and in a quiet street. The size of a family room was good although the single room size was a bit small. The only thing to improve is the breakfast because the variety is not huge.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: The hotel is in a lovely old building, in a great location, near the Eiffel Tower, which was important for our granddaughters. The staff went out of their way to accommodate us, taking care of the problems caused by booking online. They wrote emails, they called us, we worked it out. The rooms are quite small and the elevator is tiny. The gorgeous staircase is listed and cannot be replaced to make room for a larger lift. The breakfast buffet was perfectly correct. And there is an espresso machine. All one could require to start the day.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: A lovely classic style hotel in a very quiet place. I did enjoy it! You can spend time in a lobby downstairs. The breakfast room is very nice. Location is just perfect - you have Passy and La Muette metro station close to the hotel. 10 minutes by walk to see the Tour Eiffel.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Very average hotel in the heart of Paris! Staff are not welcome non French speaking people. Staff never very helpful. Breakfast was a joke! Never again. Very small room, charged for superior room. No shampoo and conditioner.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We had a great stop over in Paris with Thierry and his team. Lovely hotel in a great location ideal for exploring central Paris. The room we stayed in was clean with good size bathroom. I would recommend this hotel for families

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
Great location, comfort and very gracious staff!
Each time I stop by in Paris, I stay there, it became my pied a terre!
The breakfast room and breakfast itself are very nice.
The concierge will always be able to answer question and help to make your stay the best!
Very familiar and practical. It is the perfect hotel for business, tourists, family!
The place to stay!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: They were accomodating the whole time of our stay. Best thing is that they really look after you, we didnt stay at the hotel for 1 night because of an impromptu trip to switzerland, and forgot to tell them but they contacted us to ensure that we are safe. will definitely recommend.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Stayed here with children and had a fantastic stay. best hotel I've ever stayed in in Paris, great rooms, roomy, airy, quiet and very clean. Hotel is excellently presented and the staff are helpful and always available. Location is within walking distance of Eiffel Tower and Metro station, but has a great neighbourhood feel. Good variety of shops and restaurants close by. Will return!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
We were both happy with this hotel yet slightly let down at the same time. The hotel is in a prime position to bars, restaurants, the Metro and the Eiffel Tower and room was a decent size and clean the hotel however was very noisy - you could hear people walking around in the room above you and slamming doors.

Before we arrived, we were sent a survey about our stay so they could tailor our visit and recommend appropriate attractions and restaurants however we didn't receive anything back at all so it was a waste of time. When we asked for recommendations when we were there, they recommended very little as the receptionist didn't know the local area!?!?!?!?

We received creamer pots for coffee in the room (2 per day) however when you'd used these, the hotel wouldn't give you anymore. We asked multiple times at the reception desk to be told no every time. Very bizzare behaviour.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
Hotel is very close to Trocadero and E Tower, nice area and we waked all the way to museums too ( L’orangerie, D’Orsay and Louvre). For us this was close enough a distance, nice stroll along the river and beautiful parks and sights in Paris. On a quiet road, close to shops and metro.
The room was nice, charming, good comfortable beds, nice balcony. Breakfast more than plenty of choice. We could hear the shouty kid next door quite clearly, but that is because he was very loud. For instance we couldnt hear the parents. The bathroom though was a bit of a surprise. Whilst nicely decorated, it wasnt cleaned properly. Corners were missed by the cleaner, hair on floor as well as bathtub and the grout in between the bathroom tiles as well as the shower panel indicate that they aren't cleaned regularly. Massive let down.
The hotel stairs were another unpleasant surprise. A lot of accumulated dust, something you’d see on metro stairs. I thought that maybe there is a lot of traffic on the stairs but next morning by 11.30 when we checked out, stairs were in same condition. So clearly not cleaned daily.
Staff at reception, nice. Not exceedingly, somewhat absent, but that’s not an issue for us. Other customers though may like more of a welcoming presence.
Over all, we had an ok stay. Would I stay there again? No. For a 4 * hotel they need to do way better.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
A very quiet hotel with spacious rooms close to the subway, shops and restaurants.
We had rooms with balcony which is a big plus in the middle of Paris
Linen and towels are changed daily
The hotel staff was very friendly and helpful in recommending where to dine or what places to visit are close by
The only inconvenience is the very small elevator that does not fit more than 2 people

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We came to Paris for a mini break and the hotel was wonderful! The hotel itself is beautiful and ideally located near two metro stops and a short walk from the Eiffel tower. The staff were friendly, the facilities were great and the breakfast very nice. Would happily stay here again!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We stayed 16 nights at the hotel, and we were very pleased. first with all the employees, second with the cleaning of our room and all the hotel. It is located in a quite street off Passy rue, which we found to be a great location on the 16and. We will definitely will recomend the hotel to all our friends.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
This is a hotel with some potential, so it is with sadness that I write an essentially negative review.

Pros:
- A charming ambience, and (for a 4-star hotel in the 16th arrondissement with a great location) very well priced.

Cons:
- Very small room even by Paris standards (just big enough for the bed, had to move furniture to open the window; elevator not always working; breakfast mediocre; some apparent staff chaos.

I would have rated this hotel 3-stars not 2-stars except for the taxi we requested to the Gare Montparnasse. Instead of a taxi, they provided a supposed "hotel car" at a fixed rate of 35 Euros (a taxi would have been about half that probably). A small thing, but I felt ripped off, and indicative of what you might expect should you decide to stay here.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: I arrived in Paris originally for a one-week stay, but after a slew of sensational days, and an unexpected desire to stay, I re-booked for a whole extra week! Everyone, especially the front desk worker Delphine, was magnificent when it came to anything I might need or help with planning days. If I wanted to venture out or need ideas of where to venture out, the staff was more than helpful and even had the genuine desire to help book a car. It was from top-to-bottom a magnificent time. Plus, the location—the location could not have been better! Coming from New York City, and having it be my first time in Paris, I LOVED how close we were to the Eifel Tower (it was spectacular to walk outside and see it shimmering from the hotel!), but far enough from the "true" tourism where I felt "unsafe" (if I ever were too!). (With that said, you should note that to see the Eiffel Tower in front of you is a bit of a hike, roughly 15 minutes. Not a bad walk, just a tad farther than expected, but that didn't bother me!) I could write a novel about how positive this experience was—or how fantastic the little croissant store was around the corner— but I shall save us all the trouble and say: Book, book, book! I am already eyeing my next trip back!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
We booked this hotel as it was close to our daughters who we were visiting in Paris.

We were happy on arrival and at our prompt check in. The room while small was just perfect with a large bathroom. We also had a balcony which was a lovely surprise.

Breakfast was included in our rate and very nice.

Location was perfect for what we wanted with plenty of nearby restaurant's and it is very close to the Eiffel Tower area. Passy is a nice area with cafes and a metro.

Hotel was overall very nice, clean, comfortable and the staff were polite and helpful. I would happily book and stay again.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We stayed a here for a family holiday for 3 nights it was a great hotel in a great location very close to the Eiffel Tower and some great shops, Metro and restaurants near by. Definitely would stay again

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
Room crowded with three people. Good shower! Very kind night watchman.
Thank goodness for the elevator with our luggage. Lovely bakery just around the corner!
Good parking garage at walking distance on main road.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: I really loved the location, walkable to Effiel tower and Trocadero, little shops around and near the metro, front desk was sweet and helped with anything questions we had in regards to our travels. I would absolutely recommend this hotel!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
The location is good. 10 minutes walk to subway, different stations available. plenty of stores, restaurants, bakeries, and very important, pharmacies with fast Covid test for traveling.
the hotel is located in a quiet street. The staff was friendly. The room was good size and clean, with a nice balcony. the only was the walls are thin, so you can hear people in other rooms and very loud when they close their door, very annoying in the morning if you are trying to sleep.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: The hotel is in good location, very close to Eiffel tower. The staff are very friendly and helpful, they helped us even before the trip to arrange transportation. Room is clean and good. I am so impressed with the hotel and staff here and definitely will stay again this hotel when visiting Paris again.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We stayed for the weekend.. all females from one family, celebrating a 21st Birthday.. this little gem was a stones throw from the Eiffel Tower in a lovely area with local shops bars and restaurants ! We were made to feel so welcome special mention for the lovely lady who ran the kitchen.. we had fresh coffee and pastries on arrival waiting for our early check-in. Rooms were clean and spacious with a lovely addition of small Juliet balconies. A special mention for “Fedel” the night manager .. nothing was too much trouble ! And made our stay extra special .. the hotel also managed to arrange a meal reservation at a local restaurant as we decided at last minute we wanted to stay local on the Friday evening. We would definitely return and recommend to our family and friends.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
We stayed three nights two adults + two young kids
Well located and human sized.
Big room (for an hotel in Paris). Well furnished.
Room and bathroom were super clean.
Nice breakfast.
We warmly recommend.
Kids friendly

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Wonderful hotel in Paris. On a quiet street, but close to shops and metro station. Rooms had everything that was needed. Staff was very helpful and nice. Breakfast was also very good. Would stay there again.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Two nights stay for medical visit to a clinic nearby. Small clean hotel with small elevator, spacious room (for European standards), spacious bathroom with tub, and good linens. The room was equipped with USB chargers, desk, big screen TV, small fridge, kettle, instant coffee, tea, temperature control, and double pane windows. There are many shops and eateries in the neighborhood at walking distance. The check-in and check-out were fast with efficient, bilingual, and friendly staff. It is walking distance to the Eiffel Tower. The cons are, that the breakfast is expensive 19.00 euros per person. In addition, the “self-parking” is not in the premises. It is an 8-10 minutes’ walk (with suitcases, is not practical), and the cost is 35.00 euros per day. The hotel description should state this. We suggest making a deal for their guests with the parking management for a reduced rate. The wood paneling ads charm to the Lobby but the area is too dark. We suggest better lighting. We could not connect to the hotel’s Wi-Fi. We recommend this hotel and would stay here again when visiting the clinic.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
It’s in a nice neighborhood but it’s not central
It’s near to many major attractions but not all are ‘walking’ near
But the hotel itself is cute
Elevator is tiny
The room was clean
Overall a comfortable stay

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
We loved our stay at Best Western Trocadéro. The staff were all very friendly. The room was a bit small for 3 adults but we didn’t spend much time in the room so it was fine for us. The bathroom was beautiful and well equipped. The best thing about this hotel is the location. A teeny bit off the beaten path made for a quiet place to sleep but close enough to attractions and transportation for convenient sight seeing. And the neighborhood was a great place to shop, eat and browse!

The only suggestion I would make is to offer free coffee. The instant coffee in the room didn’t cut through the morning fog for us and the breakfast, although good was pricey and we preferred to check out neighborhood dinning options.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: The hotel is close to the Eiffel tower and the bus to and from the airport. Nice shops are around. So, room and location were ok, desk person also ok but cleaning not adequate with respect to price. Found hair in the tub. Yet the atmosphere was quite cozy and breakfast very satisfactory.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
The rooms are very small and really need renovation.
The phone in the room was broken so it was difficult to get service. Not a business hotel as there is limited room service and the breakfast is really bad, not much on the menu, no good coffee machine.
Most of the staff was helpful but some were really not. Difficult to get a food delivery or any delivery to the room. Which is very frustrating when there is no good room service options.
Good location, close to OECD office, but I will not go back.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
The place was excellent minus one male employee(Fadhel) who is of no help. Doesn’t know anything about the neighborhood- gave incorrect information- sent us the wrong way- LOSER!
we asked for an extra blanket and he basically gave a sheet....dead space - . just an aggravating example of the type of employee you don’t want! Especially after a long day enjoying this beautiful city!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We had an amazing time in Paris staying at this hotel. The receptionist Laura was very kind and helpful. Very near to the tour and the center of the city. We would definitely repeat on our next trip to Paris.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: If you want to stay at a charming place with a delicious breakfast, look no further! My family and I felt welcome and at home. Everyone at this hotel is friendly and kind. There was a very cozy sitting room with comfy couches to relax on also. We had a lovely stay here! Thank you!!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
Came for an overnight to join friends, on January 3rd, this place is very quiet, and we were very impressed by the quality of the lady in reception, professional, polite, helpful, everything I thought Paris had abandoned years ago!
Room was lovely, especially the bed linen.
Good location too.
Will return when we can.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Excellent and friendly service. Thank you! Basic shops and restaurants near the hotel. Quiet place. OECD buildings near just 10 minutes walk. To Eiffel 15 minutes walk. Breakfast was good and healthy. Wifi nothing to complain. Clean and fresh rooms.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: We found the hotel to be well located. Rooms were very good and included a refrigerator. The breakfast was adequate and the service was good. The staff was friendly. Only problem is the shower is slippery with no hand rail or safety mat in the tub. Very difficult to get in and out of the shower. An easy correction to make.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: I visited this hotel on business in Oct 2019 and was very pleased with the size of the room, its comfort and cleanliness. It is well situated and close to the OECD complex. The bed was very comfy and the room spacious by Parisien standards. The hotel has the smallest lift I have ever been in, with two people (at most) fitting. It has a breakfast service (which I didn't use) which is €20 but no lunch or dinner service. There are plenty of good options for both locally at reasonable prices! Service was friendly. I would visit again and recommend.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: I was expecting a double bed and rather small room as that seems the norm for Europe. But to my delight, we were given a very spacious room with a king size bed. The room was very clean and room service kept it that way for our entire eight day stay. The wardrobe was large enough for both me and my wife's clothes with room to stow our suitcases. The air/heat worked very good. It was fun having a balcony. We did not eat breakfast at the hotel so can not speak to that. The staff was very friendly and helpful. The hotel is close to a Metro station and other desirable destinations yet is on a quiet street close to good shopping. I would definitely stay here again

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Great customer service, nice clean rooms, room service available, has a bar, it is also located near Eiffel tower, Trocadero, etc, I highly recommend this hotel and if I visit Paris again, I would stay there for sure.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: The location is what really distinguishes this hotel from others. It's a reasonable walk away from the Eiffel Tower, with clean and comfortable lodging. Definitely coming back here for our next visit!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Beautiful, clean hotel within walking distance to many Paris sites including the Eiffel Tower. Also walking distance to a Hop On & Off Bus stop. Found a wonderful bakery just around the corner. Delicious cafe close by as well (Aéro). Room was cozy with a cute Juliet balcony. Staff were all friendly and helpful. As with most European hotels, the elevator and halls were tiny...just expect that everywhere.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
We picked the hotel because of its location.
It is walking distance (or one subway stop) from Place du Trocadero, the best place from which to view the Eiffel tower.
The hotel itself is quite comfortable, clean and elegant.
Buffet breakfast is very good (except perhaps for the undercooked bacon - by American standards anyway). The ability to cook your own soft boiled egg was great.
I'll be going back!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: I enjoyed my stay at this quaint hotel. Room is a great size! Comfortable beds and air conditioning was a plus. Desk staff is very kind and helpful. I recommend this hotel especially if your new to Paris France. If your not fluent in French, they speak English and this made it much easier for us. Lots of great shopping and a few kids shops just down the road. It's in walking distance of Eiffel tower and other monuments. I would recommend hotel 100%

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
Overall, excellent 4-star hotel (I would reserve the 5 star in this city for the highest level amenity/elaborate hotels). Meaning this property is excellent for it's level.

Rooms - comfortably sized very clean rooms, nice amenities, spacious bathroom in the larger family room. Air conditioning worked well. No concerns.

It's a historic building, so there's a very small, fully adequate, elevator, so bring a scant amount of patience if you are unwilling to climb the spiral staircase. It is not busy, so the wait is never too long.

Staff - friendly desk service, helpful with plans, housekeeping did well and kept the room well appointed with the amenities during the stay.

Location - for us it was very good - we loved being so close to the Eiffel tower by a nice comfortable walk. The nearby access to small stores, lots of small eateries and a grocery store was excellent. Felt safe all the time even out late at night. Easily accessible to metros.

I would stay here again as we really enjoyed the neighborhood.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: As the name implies, this hotel is located just across the Seine from the Eifel Tower within 15 minutes walking distance and 10 minutes to the Trocadero metro station. The hotel staff was very helpful and agreeable, the continental breakfast was very nice and our room was pleasant enough while not extravagant.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Great neighborhood, great air conditioner staff was helpful. Wish king size bed had king size mattress. Bring your own washcloth. Would recommend without hesitation. Price very competitive with other hotels and central location,

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
The staff were friendly and quickly responded to all my needs.

They provide breakfast, consisting of meat, fruit, cereal and pastries.

Restaurants and other shopping are in close range.

The hotel is within walking distance of the Eiffiel Tower.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
Friendly helpful staff
Room big enough for 4 and very clean
Double sink in bathroom which was great with 4 of us in room
Short walk to metro and walking distance to Eiffel Tower
Air conditioning worked great - we were there during a heat wave
Breakfast not included and a bit pricey but plenty of places to walk to for breakfast
Lots of shopping near by

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
My wife and I stayed here for 8 days on our honeymoon and I'm so happy we did! Here are just a few things we loved the most:
First, the location was PERFECT for what we were looking for. The hotel is tucked away on a quiet little side street from the Rue de Passy, so you don't get any kind of loud traffic noise. But once you're outside and you walk the 100 feet to the Passy, you have everything your heart desires: patisseries, shops, restaurants, a relatively close metro stop. If you turn left and start walking, you'll be in front of the Eiffel Tower in 10 minutes. It was fantastic!
Second, this was one of the cleanest hotels - not just European hotels - that I've ever stayed in. My wife is a total clean freak and she was very impressed. There was no cigarette smell and great air conditioning, which were both HUGE pluses for us. The bathroom was small by American standards but it was well arranged, clean, and did the job. I've read several people's reviews that complain about the small elevator. I'm just thankful the hotel has an elevator as we stayed on the 7th floor. Being able to send our luggage up with my wife was a lifesaver.
Last but not least, the staff were great to work with and very friendly. Our safe ran out of battery and the manager came up and was super helpful and friendly. When we asked the front desk for any recommendations for dinner or directions to attractions, they were more than accommodating.
I cannot recommend this hotel enough - seriously, unless you want to hear car horns and traffic all night, I don't think you could get a better hotel closer to any major Paris attraction.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Great helpful staff with very comfortable rooms, beds, and large bathrooms. Breakfast was great and reasonable. Easy walking distance to main attractions (Eiffel tower) and lots of local great cafes for meals.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Would give 6 stars if I could. The hotel exceeded our expectations with their friendliness and help in getting around Paris. Fadhel went over and above in making us feel at home. The room was small but standard in Paris. Location is excellent. Short walk to Eiffel Tower, supermarket and restaurants. Would definitely stay here again when visiting Paris. ******

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
We had a family of five stay in two rooms for 3 nights. The rooms are small, to US standards, but they used the space efficiently. We did not feel confined and we enjoyed our stay there. The location is in a great spot and walkable to many tourist locations.
I would also suggest to try the morning breakfast, at least the coffee and a croissant!
The staff could not be more helpful and spoke English to help us through our broken French. Haha. It was a nice experience and would go back again. Vive France!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Lovely place near Paris best places. Walking distance to stores and restaurants. Quiet, safe, but near to the action. Staff was incredibly friendly. We Love it. June is the best during summer time as weather is between 70 to 80.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: Excellent location, service was impeccable as we're the rooms. Great restaurants nearby, walking distance to many iconic locations. The neighborhood is safe for a family to walk in the evening and not overcrowded. Hotel staff and management saw to our every need/question without pause.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: This is a perfect hotel in a beautiful residential area. At the same time, it is close to the Metro, restaurants, stores, and the Eiffel Tower. We had a family room, which was very spacious. The room had a king size bed and two twins for the kids. The bathroom had two sinks! The staff are lovely and very helpful. We did not eat breakfast at the hotel because there were so many wonderful boulangeries and patisseries nearby. We could not have asked for a better place to stay during our visit to this amazing city!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
We had an amazing stay from the minute we arrived until the minute we left. My sister, niece, and I do a trip each year and this year was the first out of the country for my sister and niece. The hotel did their best to meet every single wish we had to make sure our stay was special. There were many questions and lots of tweaks to our plans and the management of this hotel showed such incredible patience with us it was amazing! The also helped to make sure we got a room with a balcony. We had champagne on our first night in the area downstairs and each morning a beautiful breakfast. Vincent at the front desk was fantastic and made sure we knew how to get to the best places and he was there to greet us each night. We loved staying here and will be back again. The hotel had an excellent location, was incredibly clean, in a beautiful building, on a quiet street, and within walking distance of the Eiffel tower. You will not go wrong staying here!

Thanks again everyone! You are amazing! The Willoughby's and Hutchinson's wholeheartedly endorse this hotel!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: This was my very first trip to Paris with my daughter and sister. After doing much research, we decided to book this hotel which was located very close to the Eiffel Tower. Being unfamiliar with the territory we were absolutely elated with our room, cleanliness and the breakfast buffet was delicious. The staff was INCREDIBLE. Vincent who worked the evening shift was so friendly and informative but not negating everyone else who worked there whos names I cannot remember. If I ever go back I will definitely stay here again. They definitely made my first trip to Paris unforgettable.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews:
We chose this hotel for its location, being within easy walking distance of the Eiffel Tower. The route to the tower was lined with lovely shops and a path by the river also. From this hotel you can walk to the Arc de Triomphe which we enjoyed, buying dinner on the way in one of the restaurants.

Our room had a balcony, spacious bathroom and minibar. It was clean, there were lovely robes and I slept very well in the bed.

We received a complementary half bottle of champagne for our celebration which was very generous and well received.

The hotel was private and quiet and we enjoyed the French style of the hotel, lovely frontage and decoration.

Breakfast was included in our room rate and was a nice buffet style arrangement. My husband was thrilled to have bacon as there was none on the Eurostar the previous morning! I was pleased to see so many pain au chocolat.

We would definitely stay here again and would recommend it to others.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: I have stayed at this hotel a number of times. It is situated in a quiet street, just off Rue de Passy. The rooms are of varying sizes, but I have never had an uncomfortable one. The beds are very comfortable, with crisp linen. The curtesy tray was very welcoming, especially as I arrived at 23:30. Rooms have a stocked fridge. Reception and management are always welcoming. It is close to two metros, Passy and La Muette, very close to Passy Plaza. There are lovely restaurants in the area, and within walking distance.

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: I have stayed at this hotel a few times over the years and recommended it to dozens of friends since my first stay in 2009. Its a quaint hotel in a great location. Only 10 minutes walk from the Trocadero for fantastic eiffel tower views but only seconds from lots of shops, restaurants and patisseries. On this occasion my husband and I were travelling with our 2 small children. We had a good sized room (particularly for Paris) with a camp bed and sofa made up for the kids. The bathroom was big with a nice bath for the kids and the rooms are lovely. The staff are all extremely friendly and helpful and I would highly recommend a stay at Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour!

hotel: Best Western Premier Trocadero La Tour
reviews: I arrived at 6 am after flying all night. I was immediately greeted by a kind man who made sure I was comfortable while I waited for him to finish with the person checking out. It didn't stop there. Each person went out of their way to get me into my room early(which I didn't request in advance). They went above and beyond my expectations!! I walked a little over a mile to the Eiffel Tower and Seine river. Taxi service in this area is abundant. Local shopping, cafes, attractions and activities are all nearby. Excellent place that I would stay at again.
